               <msContents>
                  <summary>Draft of a petition from Panopolis (modern name: Akhmim), Egypt, written on papyrus. Written by Aurelius Petechensis, priest of Panopolis to Salvius Synegorios about a priesthood(?) Mentions the high priest and Petearbeschinis. Papyrus belongs to the archive of Ammon, the well-known scholastikos, or lawyer</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Dimensions of fragments are 8.8 x 10.2 cm. or smaller</note>
                     <note type="general">12 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers on the recto in Ammon's hand</note>
                     <note type="general">Upper margin of 2 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 211 was formerly P.Duk.inv. G 211</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
